						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="126v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥovot ha-levavot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">חובות הלבבות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/56611468">Baḥya ben Joseph ibn Paḳuda, active 11th century </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/56611468">בחיי בן יוסף אבן פקודה</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>In the Hebrew translation of Yehudah ibn Tibon. </p>
								<p>The work begins on folio 3r, preceded by an introductory piece.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">אני <name type="person" role="scribe">אלחנן בכמ"ר יואב אליה מקורייו</name> כתבתי זה חובת הלבבות מכתבת ידי ממש ונשלם יום א ט"ו ימים לירח כסליו <date calendar="Hebrew">רכ"ד</date> השם ית' וית' שזכני לכתבו הוא יזכני לקרות בו ובשאר ספרי הקדש אני וזרעי וזרע זרעי עד סוף כל הדורות ונזכה לראות בניין בית הבחירה ונהיה מן הנכתבים לחיים בירושלם עם כל ישראל חבירים אמן.<locus n="125v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>126  folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>115</height>
										<width>85</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>126 folios (+ 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 10 leaves each, marked at the end by repeated words from the following folio.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slight worming at ends. </p>
									<p>Usage stains. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="22" writtenLines="22">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Horizontal quire catchwords in middle of lower margins, decorated. </p>
									<p>Vertical pricking visible.</p>
									<p>Horizontal ink ruling and vertical plummet ruling visible.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Initial words in square script. </p>
									<p>Last written line outside ruling.</p>
									<p>Red edges. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive and Ashkenazi semi-cursive scripts of the 15th century, occasionally punctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Elḥanan ben Yo᾿av Eliyah of Ḳorio</name>: inscribed, folio 125v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yohanan Treves</name>: inscribed, folio 126v.</p>
							<p>Folio 126v: 'Io Pelegrino Treves [...] Magio 1562'.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Hippolite of Ferrara</name>, Franciscan censor (active 1590-1609, Cremona?): inscribed with his name, 1601 (folio 126v), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">18-19, 93</ref>.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Vistorini</name>: inscribed 'Gio. Dom. Vistorini 1609' (olio 125v), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">85-87</ref>. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Jacobus Geraldini</name>: inscribed with his name, "1555. die 16 dec[em]bris revidus p[er] d Jac[obu]m Geraldini", notarized by "Caesar Belliossus curiae ep[iscopa]lis Bon[oniensis]": folio 125v.</p>
						</additions>
